::install in windows
    + check gpu
        dxdiag 

    + install cuda by local exe 
    + check install by 
        nvidia-smi

    + install pytorch by pip, copy the install command into miniconda
    + check pytorch install by
        python
        >>> import torch
        >>> a = torch.ones((3,1))
        >>> a = a.cuda(0)
        >>> b = torch.ones((3,1)).cuda(0)
        >>> a+b

    + install jupyter and d2l in miniconda
        pip install jupyter d2l
    + download d2l from zh-v2.d2l.ai
    + try one example in jupyter notebook
        /d2l-zh/pytorch/chapter_convolutional-modern/resnet.ipynb
